cs.NE, cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a power efficient implementation of neural networks on embedded devices.
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is also likely as the paper focuses on implementing neural networks on resource-constrained embedded platforms.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper proposes a Look-Up Table based implementation that takes into account the underlying architecture of the embedded hardware.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper applies the proposed implementation to image classification tasks on datasets such as MNIST, SVHN and CIFAR-10.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a modified Decision Tree approach in the binary domain to reduce power consumption.
